      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Looks the right race for A DIVA (4) who is going well, a handy winner fresh at Cranbourne before setting a very slow speed in front at Caulfield and being outsprinted late by a good mare in Terilee. That gives her plenty in the tank heading into this and she draws for every hope. COCO JEN (5) resumes with a good overall profile. She went to the paddock a winner at Moonee Valley and is yet to miss the quinella from six starts. First up at a mile is a tiny niggle but she should go on with it this time in. THIS TIME GIRL (7) put in a better effort at Cranbourne last time when well backed and won't need to improve much to be figuring again here. BON MISTRESS (3) got home well fresh in a good race, have to respect off that.",
